caption.p:
Effects of L. regularis (Lr) on diabetic-induced changes in hepatic enzymatic activities including superoxide dismutase (SOD), catalase (CAT), glutathione peroxidase (GPx), glutathione reductase (GR), and glutathione-S-transferase (GST). Data were expressed as mean ± SEM ( n = 6) and analyzed using one-way ANOVA followed by Student–Newman–Keuls as a post hoc test.
∗ Control vs STZ group; #STZ vs Lr (150) or Lr (300). P values are considered significant when
∗ or # P < 0.05,
∗∗ or ## P < 0.01, and
∗∗∗ or ### P < 0.001.
